# Shoe Shopping App – Wireframe to Prototype

## Project Overview
This project focuses on designing a mobile shoe shopping application by transforming low-fidelity wireframes into an interactive prototype. The goal was to create a user-friendly, visually appealing, and smooth shopping experience that helps users browse, explore, and purchase shoes easily.

## Objective
The main objective of this project was to understand the UI/UX design process from wireframing to prototyping and create an engaging shopping interface.

## Design Process

### 1. User Research
Basic research was conducted to understand user preferences and shopping behavior. Users needed:

- Easy product browsing
- Simple navigation
- Quick product selection
- Smooth checkout experience

### 2. Wireframe Creation
Low-fidelity wireframes were created to establish:

- App structure
- Screen layouts
- Navigation flow
- User interactions

The wireframes focused on functionality before visual styling.

### 3. Prototype Development
The wireframes were converted into an interactive prototype using Figma.

Prototype interactions included:

- Screen transitions
- Navigation between pages
- Button interactions
- Product selection flow
- Shopping journey simulation

## Features

- Home screen with shoe collections
- Product categories
- Product detail page
- Shoe selection interface
- Add to cart functionality
- User-friendly navigation
- Interactive prototype flow

## Tools Used

- Figma
- UI/UX Design Principles
- Prototyping Tools

